UNITED STATES of America, v. SECURITY-FIRST NATIONAL BANK OF LOS ANGELES, Executor of the Estate of Wm. R. Campbell, Deceased. No. 8960. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 19, 1938. Ben, Harrison, U. S. Atty., and E. H. Mitchell, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. Flint & Mackay, Wesley L. Nutten, Jr., and George G. Witter, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

' Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
